manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Feel the Rush of Ripjaws V Ripjaws V series DDR4 DRAM memory is designed for sleek aesthetics and performance, making it an ideal choice for building a new PC system or for upgrading your system memory.

Experience DDR4 Performance Available in a wide range of frequency options, Ripjaws V series lets you enjoy a computing experience at DDR4 speeds for gaming, video & image editing, rendering, and data processing.
Rigorously Tested The Ripjaws V DDR4 memory series is tested under G.SKILL's rigorous validation process to ensure outstanding quality.

XMP 2.0 Support Just set and go. Programmed with the latest Intel XMP 2.0 profiles, the only thing between you and overclocked performance is a simple BIOS setting. (*Enable the XMP profile in the BIOS to reach up to the rated overclock speed of this memory kit. Maximum memory speed and system stability depends on the capability of the motherboard & CPU. The memory kit will boot at the SPD speed when BIOS settings are at default.)

42mm Module Height Designed with a 42mm module height, the Ripjaws V series memory is ideal for use with large CPU coolers. (*Please check the specifications of your CPU cooler for actual height clearance.)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Don’t let the Intel word scare you - Works perfectly in my AMD system.
reviews.reviewText: I’ve bought 8 sticks of this memory (various sizes/timings) all have worked perfectly at 3600mhz with my AMD 5950x CPU. currently rocking 128GB.i always let memtest86 run at least 3 to 4 passes and this is quality ram at a decent price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Ripjaws are great. G.Skill RAM has always been my go-to for decent quality sticks. They're doing exactly what they're supposed to and I haven't run into any issues with any of the sticks I've installed over the years.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Solid Performance - after a bit of noodling
reviews.reviewText: New build - Ryzen 5600G, Radeon 6600 XT, Gigabyte B550 UD AC. Not a screamer, but still pretty decent for casual gaming and music audio work station.Was up and running in minutes with the fresh build, but started getting crashes, bsod immediately. Proceeded to update all drivers on new W11 install, nothin. I thought maybe maybe the power supply wasn't up to snuff, then I ran mem test. Immediate mem errors.Moved the sticks from slots 1,2 to slots 3,4 and wham, no errors, crashes, bsod's. ( or maybe I moved it from 3,4 to 1,2) Either way, that fixed the issue. Mem tested with zero errors after moving the sticks, and been running flawless for almost a week. Gonna buy two more 32G sticks.Hope this helps.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 22, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Stable and Fast on B450 with a 5950x
reviews.reviewText: I have an odd setup but long story short my 32GB’s of 3200Mhz RAM from a compedator went unstable at anything but JDEC 2133mhz after two years of use and i needed more RAM now too (game dev i tell yeah, its demanding). So i sought a new kit and settled on this kit, Ripjaws 64GB 3600mhz and could only be happier if i had more of it!XMP worked flawlessly to get this RAM up to speed on my motherboard and it survived several nights of memory testing to validate stability. The performance boost from running RAM that is 60% faster than my last kit, and lets me run the Infinity Fabric on my Ryzen 9 5950x also 60% faster, has been quite a surprise to my minimum frame rates in games. But more importantly, has speed up software compiling significantly, light baking, and build compiling in unreal engine. The bump to 64GB’s from 32 has also has helped a lot with dealing with Houdini and Unreal Engine 5’s penchant for eating RAM. Its been so nice to have stable and fast RAM again!I would highly recommend this kit to any Zen 3 Ryzen build!———-Update a year later and the kit is still running flawlessly! Picture is from the setup it is used in, a DR. Zaber Sentry 2.0.

Reviewed in the United States on November 30, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Gets the job done
reviews.reviewText: What bothered me about this item the most is that it was poorly packaged and can be left out there in the freezing cold/blistering heat and that may affect its performance once u install it. The original packaging is the type that u can open and close anytime so I would not classify it as Sealed. The RAM sticks are secured inside the packaging but it can be resold as supposedly "New". The only thing I felt good about it is that the stickers on the RAM told me they were manufactured in October 2021, and I bought them in November 2021 but even then that doesn't guarantee anything, so u have to kind of just believe that ur not being taken for a fool. After thinking that I broke my computer because I did the BIOS update everyone recommends (my computer would not take me to the start screen anymore, it was stuck in some type of recovery mode) the XMP profile finally showed that these were indeed 3600 but u may get an error that they are 2600 or something of the like, like I did. I'm more of a software guy (not hardware) so I took me a bit longer than it should have to get these RAM sticks going. If u install them as u should (read as many reviews as u can to understand the process) (unless u know exactly what ur doing) they are pretty plug and play. Good luck.
